conclusion: The graph shows velocity v on the y-axis and time t on the x-axis.
Object A's velocity decreases over time, forming a downward curve.
Object B's velocity increases over time, forming an upward curve.
At time t1, both objects have different velocities.
Acceleration is the rate of change of velocity with respect to time.
To determine if objects A and B have the same acceleration at t1, compare the slopes of their velocity curves at t1.
At t1, the slope of Object A's velocity curve is negative.
At t1, the slope of Object B's velocity curve is positive.
Since the slopes of the velocity curves at t1 are different, objects A and B do not have the same acceleration at t1.
